:: J [HKUJ] {"position":"975,3475","size":"100,100"}
(align:"=><=")+(box:"X=")[Lake Ad Excellentiam
]

This school lake is located in Chung Chi College of The Chinese University of Hong Kong, sandwiched between Chung Chi Hall (Chung Chi Dining Hall) and Lingnan Stadium, formerly known as the "Lotus Pond". The name of the lake is "Uncircumcised", which implies the meaning of "not yet complete, we must continue to strive for perfection", echoing the motto of Chung Chi College, "Stop at Perfection". "The meaning connotates with the school motto, which is the spirit of self-improvement with perfection as the eternal ideal.

<img src= https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0c/Lake_Ad_Excellentiam_201602.jpg/1920px-Lake_Ad_Excellentiam_201602.jpg>


Meanwhile, on November 12, 2003, the 137th anniversary of Dr. Sun Yat-sen's birth, the University of Hong Kong (HKU) held an unveiling ceremony for a bronze statue of Dr. Sun Yat-sen at the Lotus Pond. The bronze statue commemorates the 80th anniversary of Dr. Sun's visit to the University of Hong Kong. Professor Lung Ping-yee of the Department of Architecture, the Chairman of the Antiquities Advisory Board at that time, was responsible for the project. As the convenor of the project, he formed a working group with several professors and experts from the University. He visited various places to collect information and find a sculptor before finally choosing the work of Professor Szeto Siu-Kwong, who created the sculpture - in the form of the appearance and costume of Dr. Sun's visit to the University of Hong Kong. The sculpture is made of bronze, weighing one ton, 1.2 times the size of Dr. Sun Yat-sen's life-size, and took three years from conception to completion.

<img src= https://scontent-lhr6-1.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.6435-9/125182845_2760984004179067_8542575330106600386_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_p960x960&_nc_cat=109&ccb=1-7&_nc_sid=5f2048&_nc_ohc=MUnVhTljnbAQ7kNvgH6JAE1&_nc_ht=scontent-lhr6-1.xx&oh=00_AfCO63or1nxzRMWw0S9zpv1SONgASZaazjxmeFvQ5TUigg&oe=66627547>


HKU recognizes Dr. Sun Yat-sen as one of its most distinguished alums for his selfless dedication to his country and people. HKU has erected a memorial statue of Dr. Sun to reflect his image and encourage students to strive for excellence and contribute to society. 

<img src= https://scontent-lhr8-2.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.6435-9/124982748_2760984027512398_8131742428749745088_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_p960x960&_nc_cat=106&ccb=1-7&_nc_sid=5f2048&_nc_ohc=wtNu7JUMzW0Q7kNvgHDWcE3&_nc_ht=scontent-lhr8-2.xx&oh=00_AfAr-RzNXWDwAKZinb40urBj_8Ht8_4fVf1w0WQEqYW0fg&oe=66626310>




