:: W [HKU1] {"position":"750,3375","size":"100,100"}
(text-colour:grey)+(bg:(hsl:34,1,0.951,0.7))[On March 16, 1910, Sir Frederick Lugard, the then Governor of Hong Kong, laid the foundation stone for the University.

On March 30, 1911, the University was first established in Hong Kong as a self-governing body of scholars under the University Ordinance.

On March 11, 1912, the University was inaugurated. The Faculty of Arts, Engineering and Medicine was the first to be established.]

<img src=https://www.hku.hk/f/page/7546/270p333/history@750.jpg >

(text-colour:grey)+(bg:(hsl:34,1,0.951,0.7))[The Faculty of Medicine was developed from the Hong Kong Chinese College of Medicine, which was founded in 1887. The most famous alumnus of the Faculty was Dr. Sun Yat-sen, the "Father of the Nation".

In December 1916, the University held its first degree conferment ceremony, and only 23 students graduated.

Ten years after its establishment, the University of Hong Kong admitted female students for the first time.]

