Wu Guanzhong (1919-2010) spent his early years practising traditional Chinese ink painting before venturing into the colourful field of oil painting. After studying in France, he deliberately returned to China and devoted his life to exploring the fusion of Chinese and Western aesthetics. Wu Guanzhong lived and worked in Hong Kong. Hong Kong provided him with the cultural heritage of Western and Eastern aesthetics. This collection exhibits his work in three primary colours in Chinese ink: white, black and grey.

