:: sculpture [Square] {"position":"900,1600","size":"100,100"}
(bg:(hsl:210,0.8039,0.5,0.4))[Neon: [Bauhinia in Bloom" is a sculpture located at the Golden Bauhinia Square in front of the new wing of the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center on the Wan Chai waterfront in Hong Kong. Sculpted according to the shape of a budding Bauhinia, it weighs 7 tons and measures 6 meters in length, width and height. It is cast in bronze with Italian gold leaf and supported by a Sichuan red granite plinth. The square base of the pedestal symbolizes the squareness of the nine states, and the Great Wall pattern in the ring symbolizes that the motherland will always embrace Hong Kong. The base is engraved with the words "Bauhinia in full bloom forever" in golden letters, symbolizing Hong Kong's eternal prosperity.]
]

<img src=https://www.chinadaily.com.cn/dfpd/lkqfwxg/attachement/jpg/site1/20110815/00221913c0920fb33a4a2e.jpg>

(text-colour:black)+(bg:(hsl:0,0,1,0.4))[You: What is the meaning of Bauhinia?(click: "What is the meaning of Bauhinia?") [ 
Neon: The Bauhinia was the city flower of Hong Kong since 1965. After the return of Hong Kong to China on July 1, 1997, the Bauhinia is the emblem of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR). The symbol on the HKSAR flag is a combination of the five red stars on the Chinese national flag and the Bauhinia.] ]


(text-colour:black)+(bg:(hsl:0,0,1,0.4))[You: When did the sculpture be transferred to here?(click: "When did the sculpture be transferred to here?") [ 
Neon: On July 1, 1997, when the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) was established, the Central Government presented a bronze statue of the Golden Bauhinia (GBS) - "Bauhinia in Full Bloom Forever" - to Hong Kong to celebrate the establishment of the HKSAR. The bronze statue of the Golden Bauhinia was placed in front of the new wing of the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center, facing the sea, and this square was also named the Golden Bauhinia Square.] ]


