"In Hong Kong, Yum Cha has become a unique culinary culture. Grannies or grandpas always push dessert trolleys along the corridors, delivering trays of dim sum! "

"However, with the start of using dim sum paper to hold the dim sum in the teahouse, only a few restaurants have set up dim sum carts. Steamers have become an even rarer appliance. It gradually becomes a past cultural symbol."

